################################################################################
# README
################################################################################

Example of using the Python implementation of ROOT to grab data from a ROOT file
and pull out specific pieces of the code. 

This example assumes that the file contains a TTree object called ``data" and 
that that TTree contains the data members referenced in the code 
(e.g. Jet_E, Muon_Px, etc.).

Usage: 

python dump_root_to_text_file.py <ROOT file>

The data files (ROOT files) can be downloaded from 

http://ippog.web.cern.ch/sites/ippog.web.cern.ch/files/HEPTutorial.tar_.gz

ROOT:
http://root.cern.ch/drupal/

TFile:
http://root.cern.ch/root/html/TFile.html

TTree:
http://root.cern.ch/root/html/TTree.html


#######
# INSTALLING ROOT
#######

    yaourt -S root

